Personal Notes:
Difficulty Setting: Hard (4/5)
This used to be the highest (and therefore hardest) difficulty in the game, until around a month or so after when
Novice (easiest) and Nightmare (hardest) were added. Nightmare made me very frustrated, so Hard is the way Alien: Isolation was meant to be played (as stated in its in-game description).

Notes: Started on hard, finished on normal.
Played main story, didn't spend as much time reading emails and such as I would have liked, mostly because of the alien.
Personal Notes: Really enjoyed this. The way all the gameplay elements blend together makes is really fun to play. Would love to play again on easy, maybe, to spend more time looking for things I missed, especially emails.

Noticed that you can bluff with the flamethrower, by that I mean you can aim it at an approaching alien, and it will stop and hesitate, expecting a blast of flame. This is useful if you have little to no fuel left for the flamethrower.
